social_posts.post_text: @kingyoungbloodmusic last night via #fujix100f. i told myself to just enjoy the show but then involuntarily hucked my body into the crowd to capture the magic. give their album Big Thank a listen — super excited for more from this band! thanks @iamjasenka & @raeisla for coaxing me out of my cave and reminding me how much i love Seattle music ❤️‍🔥 #kingyoungblood

it’s good* to be home.

*and super freakin weird. leaving the bay at the pinnacle of my photography career feels conflicting and i haven’t shared much about why i left. i missed the northwest and my family and friends and the timing was right for a bunch of reasons, but i’m definitely still in that ~in between~ phase where people keep asking if i’m looking for a “”job”” or what have you—which i am not unless you need photos (tour included plz) or wanna buy a print, in which case hmu. maybe you want a spooky mt. rainier shot? who knew she was so close? i haven’t seen her much since i’ve been home but every time i do i gasp with delight. gonna do my best to show up around here with photography more often since it’s what i love most in this life and i will never stop never stopping. i’m also still on the ultimate viewpoint hunt and am determined to get that money shot of three tree point with the mountain in the background. until next time! #threetreepoint #mtrainier

delighted to be back in the same state as my family and re-exploring the local neighborhoods 🥰

in 2015, my cousin Amy graduated high school in San Diego and moved straight into my Seattle apartment while she was still 17 years old. idk why her dad co-signed that but I'm so happy he did because aside from the fact that I had no business living with a teenager when I was 26 and freshly home from Warped Tour, Amy’s always been so cool that she forgave me for being a disaster (i think) and we've been best pals ever since. can't wait to make more memories with her and the rest of my family who are finally ~of age~ so I don't feel like everything I do might be something they have to talk about with their therapists for the rest of their lives. eeeeek! love u @soyrizoslut and thank u @thegudione for taking my camera and capturing the moments. other highlights of this particular evening included eating delicious hand-pulled noodles, indulging in wine & chocolate flights, spending no more than 30 seconds at Add-A-Ball, and the three of us crushing a Slurpee in unison ✨ #fujix100f

anatomy of a style attempt, 2009: somewhere between scene kid and poser snow bro, hoarder of American Apparel hoodies, standing on a rock by the ocean in San Diego, staring at my Sidekick instead of the beautiful landscape, and not realizing how much I would miss the comfort of that sweet real keyboard. #RIPsidekick

cleansing my phone of seemingly-infinite drafts feels good and weird and i guess i’m just gonna keep it rippin until i feel accomplished enough to move onto my music photography archives 👀

photo by mama bae @nicoledvallee

MOAR DRAFTS ft. @puptheband rippin’ Reservoir at Born & Raised. i have a couple few other reels from this fest of @aof_official if you have a lil scroll. i’m finally running out of semi-watchable videos to post and guess i have to start living in the present again soon? where’s the fun in that?!

baby’s first dump: chaos mode. big month of art and friends and tattoos—both receiving and witnessing—and reading and writing 10,000 words and catwalking and not having a car and learning how to karaoke songs that aren’t Forget About Dre. if you want more Frank content drop some encouragement for our screaming boi in the chat 👇

@feliciathegoat at @sasquatchfestival 2014. the pinnacle of Odd Future. i still remember being so nervous standing in the on-stage VIP zone that i didn't look at the back of my camera once. most of the images were blurry because my shutter speed was too slow. what a time to be alive. #tylerthecreator #ofwgkta

hey @eriklights remember when we hyped up your band to Justin Bieber fans waiting in line for his LA and Vegas shows and somehow convinced a bunch of people that y'all were famous to the point of them screaming for you within 30 seconds of learning who you were? wtf was that about? anyway here are some photos that make me realize 2010 was 13 years ago. the v-necks. the head massager. the smattering of music-playing devices. the scene kids with side-swoop bangs and point-and-shoot cameras. photo booth as a way of life. also i am aware that the first photo has equal parts "weird flex" and "opening scene from an adult film for emos" energy. pretty sure @jadeehlers took that one. ok i'm about to chicken out and not share these SEE YA
smidley last night in an unknown city. can someone help me out please i am very lost

finally got the money shot of three tree point with mt. rainier in the background. and by money shot i mean i paid @s.h.romano $150 to take me flying so i could take this photo. i’ll be selling prints to recoup my investment very soon—let me know if you’re interested! i planned this photo for three months and am so freakin excited that the end result turned out better than expected. the pacific northwest is a magical place 🥰 #threetreepoint #mtrainier
updated twinkly pics of @thewonderyearsband from their seattle show. it’s tradition ✨ #thewonderyearsband #showboxsodo
@microwaveatl at @elcorazonseattle — my old home away from home with some friends who have slept on my floor in multiple states 🖤 #microwaveatl

a selection of photos from Sasquatch 2014. photographed for Skype: a relationship that I swiftly ruined by telling my brand contact that I only used the app to talk to him. "you probably shouldn't tell me that." 💀💀💀 i’m sorry, Tom. i've learned a lot about disclosure in the past 9 years, usually in an emotionally and/or professionally scarring way. please tell me about a time when you totally ruined a client relationship to make me feel better plz. this is a judgment-free zone 😇 @sasquatchfestival

@m83music in seattle a few weeks ago. i have a tendency to put too much weight on how much i love an artist versus the quality of photos i share then just end up not posting anything. weird form amirite? thanks @elenastrawnphotography for the opportunity to photograph an all-time favorite. #m83

buncha double exposures of @turnoverva at @neumos_ last week. this is my entire brand now. round two at alma tonight!

#turnoverva #neumos
@lsdunes last year in san francisco. sometimes i open @scrlgallery and ask myself “why are there so many unposted collages on here?” and this is one of those times 💃🕺🏻 #lsdunes

HAPPY JASENKA DAY 🎉 🎂 🥳 my ride-or-die for 20 years, #1 photo muse, and overall wonderful human being. you effortlessly toe the line between enigma and instantly becoming best friends with everyone you meet and i admire you in so many ways. i could spend all day looking for the perfect photos to share but we’ve made so many memories even in the past 9 months that i’m keepin’ it recent. exploring San Francisco, skating around my neighborhood and taking photos in Oakland, making s’mores on the patio, getting matching tattoos on a whim, ominous tarot readings on my couch, the ultimate “adventure” packing up my loft and moving me back to Washington, getting stuck in a snowstorm in the Uhaul, being each other’s emotional support through all the shit life flings at us, causing general mayhem together between Burien and White Center, and seeing some our favorite bands and maximizing living near each other again for the first time in IDEKHOWLONG. my life would be much less of an adventure you and i can’t wait to celebrate all things Jas today!!

purse fuji became pocket fuji for @blink182 on sunday night. best show of my life. i am so happy. thank you x1000 to @johnwilliam1 for enabling this experience for me and @iamjasenka ❤️ #fujix100f #blink182

We don’t get to  D R E A M  if not for each other!!!! Thank you to the ones who make our world go round and for helping us celebrate this special week. We are still floating on a happy cloud! Thank you @kexp for hosting and inviting us to play and to @kellymason for capturing these most perfect moments we will be hanging onto forever ☁️♾️⭐️

URGENT POLL: is that a butterfly in slide two image two?? i’ve been tripping out over this for a whole day and my brain cannot fathom it being anything else. @thisispvris is the best band and i’m so happy the universe inadvertently brought us together for a few days at the beginning of their tour. what a fantastic group of humans. more from this weekend sooooon 🖤

🚨 TOMMY 🚨 the incomparable @tommygenesis rocked it in this mini-portrait sesh before her portland set. idk why i’ve always feared flash portrait photography because these light up my life with inspiration. thanks a million to @elmakias @first3agency and tommy’s team for having me out!
PVRIS in PDX. sos i’m having withdrawals plz send help. or just go catch them on their current tour and spam me with videos tysm

just another one of those “i love this band too much to decide which photos to post until long after tour is over” predicaments. i stood in the pit and gawked with glee on night one of @thrice playing TAITA in its entirety. night two was a little more productive. ironically (am i finally using this word correctly??), i love the crowd surfer moment more than almost all of my other photos ✌️ bonus fun fact: i discovered thrice in 7th grade via the first punk goes pop album on crusty old hot topic headphones #thrice #theartistintheambulance

name a more fun live band than @jfcrewfanclub — actually don’t even try because it’s impossible. they are leaving for tour in a week and powering through some unexpected lineup changes, but the show must go on! listen to Just Friends’ brand new album GUSHER and check their tour dates to see when they’ll be in your city. or else 😈 (promos taken last year while filming the music video for Fever, which i make a lil ~extra~ appearance in if you wanna take a looksie) #jfcrewfanclub #justfriends
@bigthiefmusic and their effortless coolness at marymoor last month. special thanks to the equally cool @hagfrolic for enabling this experience xoxo #bigthief

if had four teenage boys--a reality my grandma lived at one point which hurts my brain to think about--i imagine they would be more mature than what happens in the @afterwordsband group chat. happy to be here & happy to be managing these hooligans. if you are a band in the PNW and wanna book a show or planning a tour through the region and want a sick local opener, let's talk. (or if you want promos or live photos, let’s… also talk.) these dudes are ready to rip and probably won't say anything offensive onstage unless it's about each other. also hire me to market your band i am very good at saying nice things ok byeee

km vs. tokyo, as documented 90% by @numako_ and 10% by @homebillings. i flew to japan to visit friends and celebrate turning 35 in a couple of weeks (wtf) and am having the best time!! everything is adorable and i don’t wanna leave. consider this your warning that i will be talking about this trip for the rest of my life. also yes i did buy the bunny sweater and have zero regrets. still a few days left! see ya!

buncha portraits of @jakeweholt for @densmore_band. this session was so much fun and i’m forever thankful photography helps me stay connected with old friends. jake has been playing in seattle bands for as long as i’ve been a music photographer (read: forever) and i’m excited to see where he takes this project!
